'''Jearl Erwin Margaritha''' (born 10 April 2000) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Challenger Pro League]] club [[S.K. Beveren|Beveren]]. Born in the Netherlands, he plays for the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]].

==Club career==
Evolved in youth academies of [[FC Groningen|Groningen]] and [[FC Emmen]], Margaritha joined Dutch fifth division side [[VV Hoogeveen]] ahead of the [[2019–20 Hoofdklasse]] season.<ref name="vvh">{{Cite web |title=Timmerman, Rasevic en Margaritha laatste aanwinsten Hoogeveen |url=https://www.tweenul.nl/nieuws/timmerman-rasevic-en-margaritha-laatste-aanwinsten-hoogeveen |access-date=11 January 2021 }}{{Dead link|date=December 2025 |bot=InternetArchiveBot }}</ref> On 1 September 2019, he made his competitive debut for the club in a 3–0 loss to [[Alphense Boys]].<ref name="stdeb">{{Cite web |title=Seizoenstart Hoogeveen eindigt in enorme deceptie |url=https://www.vvhoogeveen.nl/113/4899/uitslagen/wedstrijd-details/ |access-date=11 January 2021}}</ref> He scored his first goal two weeks later in a 5–4 loss against [[Quick '20]].<ref name="stfg">{{Cite web |title=Collectieve wanprestatie Hoogeveen bij Quick'20 |url=https://www.vvhoogeveen.nl/113/4859/uitslagen/wedstrijd-details/ |access-date=11 January 2021}}</ref>

On 9 January 2020, Hoogeveen announced the departure of Margaritha to [[Almere City FC|Almere City]].<ref name="vvhact1">{{Cite web |title=Jearl Margaritha per direct naar Almere City |url=https://www.vvhoogeveen.nl/1/174/jearl-margaritha-per-direct-naar-almere-city/earl/ |access-date=11 January 2021}}</ref> However, it took almost two months to finalize the deal as he didn't have a contract with Hoogeveen.<ref name="vvhact2">{{Cite web |title=Overgang Margaritha van Hoogeveen naar Almere City FC op losse schroeven, zaakwaarnemer blijft hoopvol |url=https://www.rtvdrenthe.nl/nieuws/156275/Overgang-Margaritha-van-Hoogeveen-naar-Almere-City-FC-op-losse-schroeven-zaakwaarnemer-blijft-hoopvol |access-date=11 January 2021}}</ref><ref name="vvhact3">{{Cite web |title=Eindelijk is het rond: Margaritha naar Almere City FC |url=https://www.rtvdrenthe.nl/nieuws/158058/Eindelijk-is-het-rond-Margaritha-naar-Almere-City-FC |access-date=11 January 2021}}</ref> On 6 September 2020, he scored his first professional goal in his team's 6–4 win against [[SBV Excelsior|Excelsior]].<ref name="fprog">{{Cite web |title=City FC wint bizar duel bij Excelsior: 4-6 |url=https://www.omroepflevoland.nl/sport/192257/city-fc-wint-bizar-duel-bij-excelsior-4-6 |access-date=11 January 2021}}</ref>

On 4 August 2021, Margaritha joined [[Eerste Divisie]] club [[TOP Oss]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Jearl Margaritha komt TOP Oss versterken|url=https://toposs.nl/jearl-margaritha-komt-top-oss-versterken/|date=4 August 2021|access-date=4 August 2021}}</ref> On 29 June 2023, he signed for [[Azerbaijan Premier League]] club [[Sabah FC (Azerbaijan)|Sabah]] on a contract until June 2027.<ref>{{cite web |title=XOŞ GƏLDİN, JARL! |url=https://sabahfc.az/2023/06/29/xos-g%c9%99ldin-jarl/ |website=sabahfc.az |publisher=Sabah FC |access-date=29 June 2023 |language=Azerbaijani |date=29 June 2023 |archive-date=29 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230629201844/https://sabahfc.az/2023/06/29/xos-g%C9%99ldin-jarl/ |url-status=dead }}</ref>

Margaritha signed with [[Phoenix Rising FC]] of the [[USL Championship]] on 16 August 2024.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Phoenix Rising Signs Curacao International Jearl Margaritha|url=https://www.phxrisingfc.com/news/phoenix-rising-signs-curacao-international-jearl-margaritha/|last=Hill|first=Tyson|date=16 August 2024|access-date=16 August 2024}}</ref> On 4 August 2025, he signed a three-year deal with Belgian [[Challenger Pro League]] side [[S.K. Beveren|Beveren]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.skbeveren.be/2025/08/welkom-jearl/|title=WELKOM OP DE FREETHIEL, JEARL MARGARITHA!|first=Maarten Van|last=Mieghem|date=5 August 2025}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uslchampionship.com/news_article/show/1343730-phoenix-rising-announces-transfer-of-jearl-margaritha-to-belgium-s-s-k-beveren|title=Phoenix Rising announces transfer of Jearl Margaritha to Belgium’s S.K. Beveren|first=USLChampionship com|last=Staff|date=4 August 2025|website=USL Championship}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in the Netherlands, Margaritha is eligible to play for Curaçao through his heritage. In November 2020, [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]] head coach [[Guus Hiddink]] named Margaritha in 23-man squad for one week's training camp.<ref name="cuwtc">{{Cite web |title=DEZE EERSTE DIVISIE-SPELERS KONDEN REKENEN OP EEN OPROEP VOOR HUN NATIONALE ELFTAL |url=https://www.elfvoetbal.nl/binnenland/279874/deze-eerste-divisie-spelers-konden-rekenen-op-een-oproep-voor-hun-nationale-elftal |access-date=11 January 2021}}</ref>

Margaritha made his debut for Curaçao on 7 September 2023 in a 1–0 defeat to [[Trinidad and Tobago national football team|Trinidad and Tobago]].<ref>{{cite web|title=The Opposition: Curaçao|url=https://www.wearehullcity.co.uk/news/2024/march/20/the-opposition-curacao/|date=20 March 2024|access-date=22 April 2025}}</ref> He scored his first four international goals for Curaçao on 15 November 2024 in a 5–0 win over [[Saint Martin national football team|Saint Martin]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Curaçao boekt ruime overwinning op St Martin uitblinkende Margaritha|url=https://nu.cw/2024/11/16/curacao-boekt-ruime-overwinning-op-st-martin-uitblinkende-margaritha/|date=16 November 2024|access-date=22 April 2025}}</ref> In June 2025, he was named in the squad for the [[2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Rosters confirmed for 2025 Concacaf Gold Cup|url=https://www.concacaf.com/en/gold-cup/news/rosters-confirmed-for-2025-concacaf-gold-cup/|date=5 June 2025|access-date=11 June 2025}}</ref>

In May 2026, Margaritha was named in Curaçao's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]], the country's first-ever appearance at the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|title=Smallest nation Curacao name debut World Cup squad|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c70798249j0o|date=18 May 2026|access-date=18 May 2026}}</ref>

